that is faster than even some enthusiastic supporters of the 
plan think possible 
former us arms control director ralph earle praised the 
initiative but called bushs timetable overly optimistic 
earle who negotiated the 1979 strategic arms limitation treaty 
with the soviet union predicted the vienna talks would take at 
least two years to reach fruition 
for 15 difficult years east and west debated a cutback in 
central europe they gave up in despair earlier this year 
primarily because of disagreements over how many troops the soviets 
had in the region 
now nato and the warsaw pact are working on a larger canvas 
the vast expanse of europe from the atlantic ocean to the ural 
