<TEXT>
appleton simply cant escape the magic of 
harry houdini and local boosters hope his legacy of daring escapes 
from straitjackets and handcuffs will snare outsiders to his 
hometown 
houdini is our favorite son theres no doubting that said 
businessman tom boldt who is leading the effort to win wider 
recognition for appleton as the magicians hometown 
boosters have named a municipal park an elementary school and a 
cafe after houdini organized an annual halloween seance to attempt 
to contact his spirit and set up walking tours and museum exhibits 
to foster his memory more than 60 years after his death 
we needed something to get people to stop in appleton for a 
while said museum curator christopher miller 
previously the fox river city of 65000 was best known as a 
stopover for tourists headed to lake michigans door peninsula or 
as the hometown of the late sen joseph mccarthy who was censured 
by the senate in the 1950s 
mccarthy is really not a fun topic but houdini is all about 
fun miller said 
the campaign received a boost earlier this year when businessman 
sydney h radner 69 of holyoke mass agreed to lease his 
collection of houdini handcuffs personal letters billboards 
photographs and personal letters to millers outagamie county 
museum 
radner a magic historian and onetime performer collected the 
artifacts from houdinis brother theo hardeen in the 1930s and 
1940s 
