the mosaics each about two feet square are said to have been 
chiseled from the interior of a small church in northern cyprus 
sometime before 1982 and are considered some of the oldest 
christian antiquities 
experts see the case as a landmark in the growing worldwide 
effort by lessdeveloped nations to reclaim and protect national 
treasures 
the mosaics took a circuitous trail from the mediterranean 
island to indiana attracting an exotic cast of characters 
including reputed international art smugglers and warring greek and 
turkish cypriots 
it was a year ago when goldberg learned of the mosaics tile 
portraits of jesus as a boy an archangel and the apostles matthew 
and james 
