said she was raped and killed and her body was locked inside the 
trunk of a car left in some woods 
defeated by an 80 decision a bid by mining companies to revive 
a 5 percent cap on the royalties they pay to help finance arizona 
public schools the justices upheld a ruling by the states highest 
court that the cap established by the state legislature in 1941 
violates federal law 
the military benefits and divorce case involved a federal law 
congress passed in 1982 following a supreme court ruling that 
barred state courts from dividing military pay in divorces the 
law called the uniformed services former spouses protection act 
allows retirement pay to be subjected to alimony awards 
the high court said today that the law does not cover military 
pay veterans are allowed to convert to other purposes 
under the acts plain and precise language state courts have 
been granted the authority to treat disposable retired pay as 
community property they have not been granted the authority to 
treat total retired pay as community property said marshall 
the justice department which sided initially with mrs mansell 
changed its mind late last year and concluded that her former 
husbands interpretation of the 1982 law is correct 
the case is mansell vs mansell 87201 
