<TEXT>
chinas wild bunch rides no longer 
a gang of 400 motorcyclists that roared through the streets of 
beijing in support of prodemocracy demonstrators is the latest 
victim of a government crackdown on the protests official media 
reported tuesday 
police arrested 11 leaders of the group who were accused of 
disturbing public order the staterun xinhua news agency reported 
the flying tiger brigade that was arrogant for a while in 
the capital has been broken crowed the beijing daily mouthpiece 
of the citys communist party 
the gang also known as the ironriding guard team was a 
huge hit with the hundreds of thousands of protesters who filled 
tiananmen square earlier this month to demand a freer society 
beijing residents heartily cheered the motorcyclists as they 
repeatedly zoomed around the square exhaust flying and horns 
honking 
local authorities however were not amused 
according to the official media the motorcyclists threw stones 
and softdrink bottles at soldiers sent to beijing to enforce 
martial law they also smashed communications offices ran off with 
fuel from gasoline stations and incited workers to strike 
a traffic cop who stuck out his hand to stop the gang at an 
intersection was knifed in the palm the beijing daily reported 
the bikers shouted slogans and spread rumors to confuse and 
poison the peoples minds and kept people from getting a 
peaceful sleep the reports said 
according to initial investigations the backbone elements of 
the team included people released after serving a prison sentence 
or after receiving juvenile delinquent reeducation rascal 
ruffians and idle businessmen and workers from private 
enterprises xinhua quoted an unidentified police official as 
saying 
