<TEXT>
the hofbraeuhaus brewery which 
supplies the famous beer hall of the same name in munich is 
celebrating its 400th birthday this week 
bavarian governor max streible will tap the first keg of brew 
thursday to begin four days of public festivities at hofbraeuhaus 
brewery in the munich suburb of riem said company director gerhard 
friedrich 
oldfashioned pulling contests between teams of oxen and horses 
will also be among the attractions recalling munich as it was when 
the brewery began operating in 1589 
the world famous hofbraeuhaus beer hall in downtown munich will 
have to wait a few years to celebrate its 400th anniversary 
friedrich said that popular tourist attraction did not go into 
operation until 1602 13 years after the brewery 
the brewery produces 35 million gallons of beer a year about 
onefourth of which is exported to other countries he said 
