<TEXT>
the people of burma whose own dreams 
of democracy were crushed brutally a year ago are finding new 
inspiration in the student uprising in neighboring china 
the burmese governments response to protest was much harsher 
than chinas has been soldiers opened fire on crowds of peaceful 
demonstrators killing thousands 
in september the military banned all protest 
about a dozen students defied the ban thursday and rallied 
outside the rangoon university campus shouting slogans in support 
of the chinese protest a western diplomat reported from the 
burmese capital 
tin oo chairman of the national league for democracy the main 
