<TEXT>
black kidney recipients fare as well as whites 
transplant doctors said tuesday contradicting other studies that 
have found blacks tend to do much worse after such surgery 
even in our program back in 1982 1983 1984 they blacks 
did a little worse lately they dont and overall they do as well 
as whites said dr ingemar dawidson associate professor of 
surgery at the university of texas southwestern medical center at 
dallas 
its hard to tell why but i think the message is that we 
can transplant blacks as well as whites he said 
dr clive o callender head of the howard university hospital 
transplant center said studies encompassing larger pools of 
patients show kidney transplants are 10 percent to 20 percent less 
successful in blacks than whites 
i guess you believe what you want to said callender one of 
the nations few black transplant surgeons 
a 15 percent difference for instance was found in a study of 
more than 2000 patients who received kidneys from 1968 to 1988 at 
the university of alabama at birmingham that difference was noted 
after the advent of the potent antirejection drug cyclosporine 
said dr arnold diethelm chairman of surgery there 
the drug which suppresses the bodys natural immune system was 
approved for general use by the us food and drug administration 
in 1983 
we havent seen the advantages of cyclosporine in the black 
race diethelm said one explanation he said could be the high 
incidence of high blood pressure among blacks and other genetic 
factors 
dawidson however found blacks and whites did equally well with 
cyclosporine he said poorer success was noted among blacks when 
earlier less sophisticated antirejection medication was used 
the biggest problem is we are ignorant of the immunogenic 
system of black patients callender said until we know that 
well be stabbing in the dark 
dawidson reported at the annual meeting of the american society 
of transplant physicians that 70 percent of the centers 130 black 
patients since 1982 had functioning kidneys one year after 
transplantation that compared to a oneyear success rate of 66 
percent among 213 whites 
the success rate two years after surgery was 68 percent for 
blacks and 71 percent for whites dawidson said 
during the past two years the oneyear success rate for both 
groups has climbed to 85 percent to 90 percent according to 
dawidson ninetythree percent of the black patients were alive a 
year after surgery compared to 90 percent of the whites dawidson 
said there also was no statistical difference five years later 
about a fourth of both groups needed at least one dialysis 
treatment following the transplant operation because of delayed 
graft function dawidson said 
dr paul peters chairman of the university of texas urology 
division said careful matching of the tissue type between donor 
and recipient likely contributed to the improved success rate among 
blacks he also cited the centers experience in dealing with black 
patients 
blacks comprise nearly a third of all patients at parkland 
memorial hospital where the kidney transplants were performed 
i dont think we can take praise for better surgical 
techniques because there are plenty of places that can do it just 
as well peters said but we are familiar with the problems of 
black patients 
its difficult to know if race plays a role in the outcome of 
heart transplantation since the procedure is so rarely performed on 
blacks callender said but doctors at the university of pittsburgh 
are finding similar survival rates among whites blacks and other 
minorities 
the texas doctors have not yet studied the longterm results of 
black kidney patients the feeling elsewhere however is that 
blacks lag far behind whites over the long haul according to 
dr philip held program director of the renal research program at 
the urban institute in washington 
but what does that mean it doesnt mean transplantation is a 
bad idea for blacks held said for a black patient the option 
is not to become white his option is transplantation or dialysis 
