arab summit conference which endorsed arafats initiative and 
sought ways to end the lebanese civil war 
jibril denies involvement in the pan am bombing but he has said 
his group makes bombs similar to the one investigators believed 
exploded in the plane over lockerbie scotland on a flight from 
frankfurt via london to new york 
iran also denies involvement 
popular front spokesman fahd shrourou said on may 21 in damascus 
in decrying us allegations were not agents for iran or anyone 
else they didnt ask us theyre not allowed to ask us for such 
things 
he said that american insistence on blaming us is because 
theyve failed to get any evidence firmly linking his group with 
the pan am bombing 
diplomats and counterterrorism specialists believe jibril and 
palestinian terrorist mastermind abu nidal forged new links over 
the last year with iranian radicals and their shiite moslem allies 
in lebanon 
the radical resurgence in tehran the confrontation with the 
west over british author salman rushdies novel the satanic 
verses which many moslem say blasphemes islam and opposition by 
hardline palestinian factions to arafats initiative by the 
palestine liberation organization would provide fertile ground for 
such an alliance 
iranian parliament speaker hashemi rafsanjani asked palestinians 
this month to kill five westerners for every palestinian slain by 
israelis in the uprising in the occupied territories and to attack 
western targets 
he later claimed he was misinterpreted but his remarks were 
seen as reflecting the militancy of radicals now ascendant in 
tehran 
the diplomatic sources said evidence against the the popular 
front for the liberation of palestinegeneral command in the pan am 
sabotage is circumstantial but its there 
they cited the arrest of 14 popular front activists in west 
germany last october including a top jibril lieutenant kassem 
dalkamoni 
the men had czechoslovakmade semtex explosives hidden in a 
candy wrapper and a bomb hidden in a japanesemade cassette radio 
linked to a barometric device 
investigators have concluded the pan am bomb contained semtex 
was hidden in a cassette radio packed in a suitcase and was 
triggered by a barometric sensor 
popular front officials said the men arrested in west germany 
were heading for the middle east to attack israeli targets 
shrourou said we dont carry out attacks in europe because 
that would have a negative effect on the support of the eec 
european economic community nations for the palestinian 
struggle 
however western european governments have generally supported 
arafats efforts to negotiate a settlement with israel a move 
jibril and his fellow radicals consider a betrayal of the 
palestinian cause 
diplomats and counterterrorism specialists doubt the popular 
fronts claim it would not hit targets in europe 
police in sweden last week arraigned three men they said were 
linked to the popular front for the liberation of palestinegeneral 
command for suspected complicity in the 1985 bombing of a danish 
synagogue and similar attacks on us and israeli airline offices 
in denmark sweden and the netherlands 
