<TEXT>
suppose you were seeing a space movie you knew nothing about 
the crew of the space ship includes a black a japanese a russian 
a scot as well as a halfhuman halfspaceling a regular united 
nations 
the action is wildly improbable when the heroes find themselves 
in inescapable peril they simply request a fat guy to remove them 
to a safer place as for special effects theyre on a par with 
saturday morning tv shows and the dialogue features such cliches 
as you look as if youd seen a ghost i think i have 
captain i think i have 
now suppose you learn the movie is star trek v the final 
frontier that changes things right 
star trek has become such a modern mythology that it defies 
criticism even when the movies descend into selfparody maybe 
its better simply to report the plot and let the ticket buyer 
beware 
members of the starship enterprise crew are vacationing in 
yosemite still pristine in the 23rd century captain kirk is 
climbing the face of el capitan he slips and plunges downward 
then zip spock in his jet boots manages to rescue him preventing 
a short movie 
the crew is summoned back to the enterprise its a new model 
and chief engineer scott is still trying to get the bugs out no 
time the enterprise is ordered on a troubleshooting mission some 
religious zealots have conquered nimbus iii the planet of 
galactic peace and have taken hostages 
the ramshackle enterprise takes off and it is tracked by kirks 
archenemies the strangetalking klingons kirk escapes and he 
attacks the nimbus iii rebels kirk and party are captured and they 
encounter the leader of the rebellion a christlike vulcan named 
sybok he turns out to be spocks halfbrother 
sybok commandeers the enterprise for a flight past the unknown 
and into a strange land where he believes god lives he is sadly 
disappointed 
action is scarce while the characters engage in metaphysical 
political and personal matters william shatner takes his turn at 
directing leonard nimoy directed no iv and he performs well 
within script limitations all of the crew members satisfactorily 
do their shtick lawrence luckinbill is impressive as the 
wrongheaded sybok 
the paramount pictures release was produced by harve bennett 
with a script by david loughery from a story by loughery shatner 
and bennett the rating is pg perhaps for excitement 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
motion picture association of america rating definitions 
g general audiences all ages admitted 
pg parental guidance suggested some material may not be 
suitable for children 
pg13 special parental guidance strongly suggested for 
children under 13 some material may be inappropriate for young 
children 
r restricted under 17 requires accompanying parent or adult 
guardian 
x no one under 17 admitted some states may have higher age 
restrictions 
