<DOCNO> AP890530-0268 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
the stakes are a lot higher than they were in the 
days of sutters mill or the klondike rush but gold fever still 
drew hundreds to an international gold show that began tuesday 
anyone expecting the grizzled prospectors of yore might be 
disappointed though to find that modernday goldbugs often 
dress in pinstriped suits and care more about geophysics and 
electromagnetics than grubhoes and hammers 
despite their formal appearance however many of the mining 
company officials at the exposition said that those who devote 
their lives to the pursuit of gold are still a breed apart 
youre like a detective unraveling the secrets of mother 
nature said robert s middleton president of tarzan gold inc 
which mines gold and mineral deposits in canada but the old guys 
are kind of being phased out theyre being replaced by unemployed 
geologists 
gold miners from companies with names like galactic resources 
inc pegasus gold and rayrock yellowknife swapped tales of 
hightech mining practices like induced polarization they also 
attended lectures on such diverse topics as how to develop a 
mine and platinum star of the metals market 
but middleton and others who staked their claims behind display 
booths at the boston gold show were on the lookout for investors in 
what has been a lean period for gold 
the price of gold has been down for three years after a boom 
period on tuesday it hovered near 363 an ounce on world markets 
as a result said some gold analysts at the exposition many 
smaller companies that deal in precious metals are in precarious 
financial health while the approximately 20 major companies have 
been expanding 
gold may be in more of a bear market but the spirits of mining 
company officials tuesday were still upbeat 
were risktakers optimistic people said robert dickinson 
president of continental gold corp which discovered a major 
deposit outside vancouver british columbia in november 1988 that 
has so far yielded 4 million ounces of gold 
for some perspective south africa the worlds largest producer 
of gold produced about 60 million of ounces last year according 
to industry officials the soviet union is the worlds 
secondlargest producer followed by canada the united states and 
australia are tied for fourth place officials said 
dickinson said most of the miners and investors who attend 
expositions like the gold show consider themselves goldbugs 
a goldbug is a person who believes that because of all the 
problems in the world that an investment in gold is a protection 
against collapse and the foundation of all money said dickinson 
but its also someone who has gold fever 
these days high technology has made mining for gold far more 
sophisticated than what took place during the gold rushes in 
northern california in 1849 or in the yukon territory in 1898 
but much of the work that goes into finding a new vein is still 
backbreaking labor and surprisingly primitive 
the actual staking of the claim is pretty barbaric said 
douglas martin a miner and geologist with tarzan gold 
as martin as others explained it modern prospectors begin to 
scout possible locations by using government maps of areas near 
known gold fields then they walk the bush in chosen areas 
using simple tools to clear away brush and scrape rock outcroppings 
once they have found a likely location they use what they call 
airborne geophysical instruments mounted in aircraft to measure 
electromagnetic fields that may signal the presence of precious 
metals in the bush below 
if the sensors pick up evidence of gold the miners return to 
the ground they stake out their claim by walking a 40acre site 
and placing a post in four corners that are each 1320 feet apart 
after they receive mineral rights to the spot they go in with 
backhoes and bulldozers and drill for gold 
and when they strike gold the feeling is timeless the miners 
said 
its really a thrill said middleton who still remembers 
the dimension of a major deposit in gold he found after drilling 
one hole in ontario it was 98 feet of 256 ounces of gold he 
said 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

